subproject.description:
The initiative is designed to: 
1/ Assist transitional strategy from direct individual humanitarian assistance to sustainable human development for all communities, including refugees in Pankisi Valley, and 
2/ Strengthen the national system of protection of refugees in a broader context of democratic governance, addressing poverty and promoting sustainable human development in Pankisi Valley.
The immediate objective of the project is to ensure integrated local development and improve the lives of people in the Pankisi Valley through enhanced employment and economic opportunities, better provision of social services, and safe and secure environment. 

The project consists of the following major components: 
• Assessment of agriculture potential and market development needs;
• Development of local farmers’ production capability through provision of agriculture extension services;
• Increasing efficiency of animal husbandry;
• Creation and development of a farmers’ association;
• Development of a small dairy processing plant. 
The initiative is jointly implemented by UNDP and UNHCR.
